        Official Singles Chart on 17/2/2017

        17 February 2017 - 23 February 2017

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        My thoughts & observations on the UK charts as always…
        - ‘Shape Of You’ by Ed Sheeran remains atop the Official Charts for a sixth consecutive week. While it’s still ruling both sales & streaming, it’s lead did shrink in the former metric & it lost a lot in performance in the latter category. It is now just two weeks to go until he releases his highly anticipated third studio album, titled ‘÷’.
        - Although Ed Sheeran’s biggest competition for #1 is himself, it might not be with ‘Castle On The Hill’ anymore. The promotional single for his album is called ‘How Would You Feel (Paean)’ & has bounded to #1 on iTunes in just a few hours, so it’s possible that Ed could be replacing himself at the top next week. If this does happen, Ed would become only the fifth ever act to do so. At first listen, I would say ‘How Would You Feel (Paean)’ is better than ‘Shape Of You’, but not as good as ‘Castle On The Hill’.
        - Ed has also been announced as one of the performers for next week’s BRIT awards. Other performances come from: Katy Perry, Emeli Sande, Little Mix, Bruno Mars, Skepta & The 1975. You can watch the show live on ITV next Wednesday night.
        - ‘Human’ by Rag’n’Bone Man rebounds 5-2 this week to tie its peak position, thanks to strong increases in sales & radio. It has now been blocked at #2 for a second time, also stuck behind ‘Rockabye’ by Clean Bandit ft Sean Paul & Anne-Marie. I’m pleased to see two songs in the Top 3 that have some features of rock music in them though.
        - There’s more good news for Rag’n’Bone Man, as his debut album (also called ‘Human’), enters at #1 on the albums chart. He is the winner of the BRITS Critics’ Choice Award for 2017, following in the likes of big British names, including: Adele, Ellie Goulding & Sam Smith.
        - His debut album sold a huge 117,000 copies in its first week, making ‘Human’ the fastest selling debut album by a male act this decade & outselling the rest of the Top 10 combined. The rest of the Top 5 this week is: ‘Little Fictions’ by Elbow (1-2), ‘Rip It Up’ by Thunder (new at #3), ‘One Foot Out’ by Nines (new at #4) & the ‘La La Land’ Motion Picture Cast Recording (2-5).
        - Back on the singles chart, Rag’n’Bone Man also soars 51-25 with ‘Skin’, but other than that, there were no major climbers in the Top 40. Two songs did advance four spots though; ‘I Don’t Wanna Live Forever’ by ZAYN & Taylor Swift (9-5) & ‘Play That Song’ by Train (25-21).
        - The highest debuting song of the week is ‘Chained To The Rhythm’ by Katy Perry ft Skip Marley, starting at #7. It’s become the lead artist’s 14th Top 10 hit & her first Top 10 since ‘Dark Horse’ reached this region in late 2013. It’s a dancehall & disco song which uses a mid-tempo beat & this is well supported by the elements of synth & electric guitars. It’s a fun party song that I can’t take off repeat, but considering Sia co-wrote it & Max Martin was responsible for the production, I had high hopes going into this song anyway. It’s good to see Katy Perry back on the charts again!
        - Meanwhile, Anne-Marie earns her second Top 40 appearance as a lead artist with ‘Ciao Adios’, which is a new entry at #40. You’ll probably remember her most from her feature on ‘Rockabye’ (which spent 9 weeks at #1 last year) & has also been nominated for British Breakthrough Act at the BRIT awards next week. It’s not a terrible song, but I don’t think I’m going to really like it anytime soon; the song can easily get annoying & relative to her other songs, the vocals are a bit weaker here.
        - Also, along with Ed Sheeran’s latest single, other Top 40 debuts for next week could be: ‘Giants’ by Take That, ‘It Ain’t Me’ by Kygo & Selena Gomez (love this one!) & ‘Cold’ by Maroon 5 ft Future.
        - Thanks for reading my review! Have a good weekend everyone. :)
